OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited is committed to protecting your privacy and developing technology
that gives you the most powerful and safe online experience. This Statement of Privacy
applies to the MemNet Membership Software Web site and governs data collection and usage.
By using the MemNet Membership Software website, you consent to the data practices described
in this statement.

OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited collects personally identifiable information, such as your e-mail
address, name, home or work address or telephone number. OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited also
collects anonymous demographic information, which is not unique to you, such as
your post code, age, gender, preferences, interests and favorites.

There is also information about your computer hardware and software that is automatically
collected by OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited. This information can include: your IP address,
browser type, domain names, access times and referring Web site addresses. This
information is used by OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited for the operation of the service, to
maintain quality of the service, and to provide general statistics regarding use
of the MemNet Membership Software Web site.

Please keep in mind that if you directly disclose personally identifiable information
or personally sensitive data through OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited public message boards,
this information may be collected and used by others. Note: OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited
does not read any of your private online communications.

OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited encourages you to review the privacy statements of Web sites
you choose to link to from OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited so that you can understand how those
Web sites collect, use and share your information. OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited is not responsible
for the privacy statements or other content on Web sites outside of the OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited
and OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited family of Web sites.

OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited collects and uses your personal information to operate the MemNet Membership Software
Web site and deliver the services you have requested. OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited also uses
your personally identifiable information to inform you of other products or services
available from OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited and its affiliates. OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited may also
contact you via surveys to conduct research about your opinion of current services
or of potential new services that may be offered.

OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited does not sell, rent or lease its customer lists to third parties.
OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited may, from time to time, contact you on behalf of external business
partners about a particular offering that may be of interest to you. In those cases,
your unique personally identifiable information (e-mail, name, address, telephone
number) is not transferred to the third party. In addition, OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited
may share data with trusted partners to help us perform statistical analysis, send
you email or postal mail, provide customer support, or arrange for deliveries. All
such third parties are prohibited from using your personal information except to
provide these services to OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited, and they are required to maintain
the confidentiality of your information.

OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited does not use or disclose sensitive personal information, such
as race, religion, or political affiliations, without your explicit consent.

OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited keeps track of the Web sites and pages our customers visit within
OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited, in order to determine what OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited services are
the most popular. This data is used to deliver customized content and advertising
within OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited to customers whose behavior indicates that they are interested
in a particular subject area.

OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited Web sites will disclose your personal information, without notice,
only if required to do so by law or in the good faith belief that such action is
necessary to: (a) conform to the edicts of the law or comply with legal process
served on OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited or the site; (b) protect and defend the rights or
property of OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited; and, (c) act under exigent circumstances to protect
the personal safety of users of OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited, or the public.

The MemNet Membership Software Web site use "cookies" to help you personalize your online
experience. A cookie is a text file that is placed on your hard disk by a Web page
server. Cookies cannot be used to run programs or deliver viruses to your computer.
Cookies are uniquely assigned to you, and can only be read by a web server in the
domain that issued the cookie to you.

One of the primary purposes of cookies is to provide a convenience feature to save
you time. The purpose of a cookie is to tell the Web server that you have returned
to a specific page. For example, if you personalize OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited pages, or
register with OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited site or services, a cookie helps OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited
to recall your specific information on subsequent visits. This simplifies the process
of recording your personal information, such as billing addresses, shipping addresses,
and so on. When you return to the same MemNet Membership Software Web site, the information
you previously provided can be retrieved, so you can easily use the OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited
features that you customized.

You have the ability to accept or decline cookies. Most Web browsers automatically
accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies
if you prefer. If you choose to decline cookies, you may not be able to fully experience
the interactive features of the OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited services or Web sites you visit.

OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited secures your personal information from unauthorized access,
use or disclosure. OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited secures the personally identifiable information
you provide on computer servers in a controlled, secure environment, protected from
unauthorized access, use or disclosure. When personal information (such as a credit
card number) is transmitted to other Web sites, it is protected through the use
of encryption, such as the Secure Socket Layer (SSL) protocol.

OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited will occasionally update this Statement of Privacy to reflect
company and customer feedback. OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited encourages you to periodically
review this Statement to be informed of how OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited is protecting your
information.

OMNI Software Solutions Pty Limited welcomes your comments regarding this Statement of Privacy.
